description:
The Stranger profiles three immigrant stories and includes interviews with local and national Christian leaders.   By highlighting biblical teaching related to immigrants, sharing compelling stories of immigrants who are also evangelical Christians, and addressing some common economic and political misconceptions, The Stranger seeks to mobilize evangelical Christians to respond to immigrants and to immigration policy in ways that are consistent with biblical principles. 

Director: Linda Midgett
Starring: Derrick and Meghan Smith , Pastor Choco, Barrett Duke, Liuan Chen Huska, Bert Lemkes, Douglas Holte-Eakin, Bruce and Daine Stewart and Maria
tags: Bruce and Daine Stewart and Maria

chapters.title: Desperate, Maria calls the police anyway.
Maria and her children flee to a women's shelter.
Maria's four children are US citizens.
Douglas Holtz-Eakin was the Director of the Congressional Budget office under President George W. Bush.
Dianne is a public relations expert.
Bruce teaches critical reading skills to military intelligence.
On July 8, 2001, the Stewarts move to the US from South Africa.
The Stewarts' new petition is denied. They have two months to leave the country.
Republican Congresswoman Sue Myrick tries to stand up to the immigration bureaucracy
Bruce's military contacts write letters of support.
Michael's passport has expired, and they cannot return to South Africa.
Out of the blue, the visa is approved.
